{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}
'''''Your and My Secret''''', known in [[Japan]] as {{nihongo|lit. "My and Her Three X's"|<U+50D5><U+3068><U+5F7C><U+5973><U+306E><U+00D7><U+00D7><U+00D7>|Boku to Kanojo no Peke Mittsu|lead=yes}}, is a [[manga]] series by [[Ai Morinaga]]. The series was first published in [[Enix]]'s ''Monthly Stencil'' in January 2001, was later obtained by [[Mag Garden]] who published it in ''[[Monthly Comic Blade]]'' then ''[[Monthly Comic Avarus]]'' where it concluded its serialization in August 2011. The individual chapters were collected and released into eight [[tank<U+014D>bon]] volumes by [[Mag Garden]]. A continuation of the manga, subtitled as {{Nihongo|Extra-Part|<U+756A><U+5916><U+7DE8>|Bangai-hen}}, was serialized in Mag Garden's online magazine, Web Comic Beat's, between June 2012 and March 2013; it was later released in a single tank<U+014D>bon volume. In Japan, ''Boku to Kanojo no Peke Mittsu'' has been adapted into three [[Radio drama in Japan|radio dramas]] and a live action film. ''Your and My Secret'' follows the effeminate Akira Uehara who switches bodies with the tomboy Nanako Momoi due to an accident.

[[ADV Manga]] licensed ''Boku to Kanojo no Peke Mittsu'' and released it under the name ''Your and My Secret'' in 2004. [[Tokyopop]] later obtained the license and released the first seven volumes of ''Your and My Secret''. After Tokyopop's closure in 2011, the North American licensing was returned to Mag Garden.<ref name="Tokyopop Shutdown"/> In 2012, [[JManga]] licensed and published the eight volumes digitally. The series has also been popularized under the name ''My Barbaric Girlfriend'' due to [[scanlations]].<ref name="Jason Thompson"/> Tokyopop's localized volumes appeared on ICv2's monthly top three-hundred selling graphic novels. English reviewers have praised the series' humor with mixed reaction to the plot and characters.

==Plot==
Akira Uehara volunteers to deliver homework to Nanako Momoi, his classmate and crush.{{gnr|ch|1}} At Nanako's home, her grandfather's invention causes Akira and Nanako to exchange bodies; the invention is destroyed shortly after its use.{{gnr|ch|2}} Nanako is thrilled with the exchange as it compliments her tomboy personality; she begins dating her friend Makoto Shiina. Meanwhile, Akira's effeminate personality combined with Nanako's beauty garners the courtship of his friend, Shinnosuke Senbongi, to his discomfort.{{gnr|ch|5}}

The series continues episodically and focuses on Akira's deteriorating resolve to return to his body and his hesitation in reconciling Shinnosuke's feelings. Eventually, Akira decides to accept the new status&nbsp;quo but a new invention unintentionally reverses the exchange; the invention is destroyed after its use once again and Nanako's grandfather becomes amnesiac. On the behest of the Akira and friends, Shinnosuke begins researching on how to build a machine to reenact the exchange.{{gnr|ch|62}} Eight years later, Shinnosuke succeeds allowing the four to reunite with their respective lovers.{{gnr|Ex|6}}

===Main characters===
;{{nihongo|{{vanchor|Akira Uehara}}|<U+4E0A><U+539F><U+3042><U+304D><U+3089>|Uehara Akira}}
Akira is an effeminate male with a crush Nanako Momoi.{{gnr|ch|1}} After exchanging bodies with her, his personality and Nanako's feminine appearance causes his popularity to soar.{{gnr|ch|4}} His best friend, Shinnosuke Senbongi, learns his secret and becomes enamored with his new appearance. Initially, Akira was adamant on returning to his body and maintaining his masculinity. During the series, he reluctantly reconciles Shinnosuke's feelings and upon realizing everyone is happier with the new status&nbsp;quo, resigns to live in Nanako's body.{{gnr|ch|57}} He is voiced by [[Kenji Nojima]] in the three radio dramas and is portrayed by Shun Shioya in the live action film.<ref name="Drama 2 announcement">{{cite web| url=http://natalie.mu/comic/news/54747| title=Ai Morinaga's ''Boku to Kanojo no Peke Mittsu'' 10 year benchmark| date=August 12, 2011| publisher=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]| language=Japanese| accessdate=September 14, 2013}}</ref><ref name="Cast1">{{cite web| archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20060425023145/http://www.peke3.com/cast1.html| archivedate=April 25, 2006| url=http://www.peke3.com/cast2.html| title=''Boku to Kanojo no Peke Mittsu'' cast| publisher=Sega Link| language=Japanese| accessdate=August 22, 2013}}</ref>

;{{nihongo|{{vanchor|Nanako Momoi}}|<U+6843><U+4E95><U+83DC><U+3005><U+5B50>|Momoi Nanako}}
Nanako is an extreme tomboy with an insensitive personality. Like Akira Uehara, she becomes popular with the students and Akira's parents after the exchange due to her personality and Akira's masculine appearance. Initially Nanako intended to return to her body after having fun as a male and was very strict on how Akira treated her body.{{gnr|ch|4}} She resolves to stay in Akira's body and relents her body's ownership to Akira after she falls completely in love with her friend, Makoto Shiina.{{gnr|ch|55}} Her parents learn about the exchange and are supportive of the status&nbsp;quo as they accept Nanako's hopelessness as a female.{{gnr|ch|51}} She is voiced by [[Miyuki Sawashiro]] in the three radio dramas and is portrayed by [[Mai Takahashi]] in the live action film.<ref name="Drama 2 announcement"/><ref name="Cast1"/>

;{{nihongo|{{vanchor|Shinnosuke Senbongi}}|<U+5343><U+672C><U+6728><U+9032><U+4E4B><U+4ECB>|Senbongi Shinnosuke}}
Sebongi is Akira Uehara's childhood friend.{{gnr|ch|6}} He falls for Akira, in Nanako's body, and wholly accepts the body exchange.{{gnr|ch|19}} Shinnosuke uses his wits in order to make Akira acknowledge his growing attraction towards him. He is voiced by [[K<U+014D>suke Toriumi]] in the three radio drama and is portrayed by Taigo Fujisawa in the live action film.<ref name="Drama 2 announcement"/><ref name="Cast2">{{cite web| archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20060501231947/http://www.peke3.com/cast2.html| archivedate=May 1, 2006| url=http://www.peke3.com/cast2.html| title=''Boku to Kanojo no Peke Mittsu'' cast| publisher=Sega Link| language=Japanese| accessdate=August 22, 2013}}</ref>

;{{nihongo|{{vanchor|Makoto Shiina}}|<U+690E><U+540D><U+771F><U+7434>|Shiina Makoto}}
Makoto is a good matured girl who is Nanako Momoi's friend. She is unaware of the exchange and begins dating Nanako, in Akira's body, while maintaining her friendship with Akira, in Nanako's body.{{gnr|ch|5}} Her brother, {{nihongo|Katsupei Shiina|<U+690E><U+540D><U+52DD><U+5E73>|Shiina Katsupei}}, is overprotective of her and threatens any males who comes close to her. She is voiced by [[Rie Kugimiya]] in the three radio dramas and is portrayed by Akie Suzuki in the live action film.<ref name="Drama 2 announcement"/><ref name="Cast2"/>

;{{nihongo|{{vanchor|Manzou Momoi}}|<U+6843><U+4E95><U+842C><U+9020>|Momoi Manz<U+014D>}}
Manzou is Nanako Momoi's grandfather. He is overweight, lazy, perverted, and fails as an inventor. After the exchange, he refuses to rebuild the machine as he is happier having a feminine granddaughter who does the house chores.{{gnr|ch|6}} In the second accident which undoes Akira and Nanako's exchange, he becomes amnesiac from a head injury.{{gnr|ch|62}} He is voiced by [[Kenichi Ogata (voice actor)|Kenichi Ogata]] in the three radio dramas and is portrayed by Masahiro Sato in the live action film.<ref name="Drama 2 announcement"/><ref name="DVD credits">Credits from {{cite video| date= April 21, 2006| title=<U+50D5><U+3068><U+5F7C><U+5973><U+306E><U+00D7><U+00D7><U+00D7>| medium=DVD| publisher=[[Sega]]| id={{EAN|4974365182465}}}}</ref>

==Media==
===Manga===
''My and Her Three X's'' is written and illustrated by [[Ai Morinaga]]. It began serialization in [[Enix]]'s ''Monthly Stencil'' magazine in its March 2001 issue and published five chapters in total upon the November 2001 issue's release.<ref name="Stencil March 2001">{{cite journal| magazine=<U+6708><U+520A><U+30B9><U+30C6><U+30F3><U+30B7><U+30EB>| volume=3| number=2001| date=January 31, 2001<!-- http://web.archive.org/liveweb/http://www.koushi.biz/cgi-prog/library/book.cgi?num=001907 -->| publisher=[[Enix]]| language=Japanese}}</ref><ref name="Stencil November 2001">{{cite journal| magazine=<U+6708><U+520A><U+30B9><U+30C6><U+30F3><U+30B7><U+30EB>| volume=11| number=2001| date=September 29, 2001<!-- http://web.archive.org/liveweb/http://www.koushi.biz/cgi-prog/library/book.cgi?num=002086 -->| publisher=[[Enix]]| language=Japanese}}</ref> Afterwards, its serialization was resumed in [[Mag Garden]]'s [[Monthly Comic Blade]]'s first issue, April 2002, and published the thirty-third chapter in the October 2007 issue.<ref name="MCB 1st">{{cite journal| magazine=<U+6708><U+520A><U+30B3><U+30DF><U+30C3><U+30AF><U+30D6><U+30EC><U+30A4><U+30C9>| volume=4| number=2002| date=February 28, 2002| publisher=[[Mag Garden]]| language=Japanese}}</ref><ref name="MCB October 2007">{{cite journal| magazine=<U+6708><U+520A><U+30B3><U+30DF><U+30C3><U+30AF><U+30D6><U+30EC><U+30A4><U+30C9>| volume=10| number=2007| date=August 30, 2007| publisher=[[Mag Garden]]| language=Japanese}}</ref> Its serialization was transferred to Mag Garden's [[Monthly Comic Avarus]] beginning in the November 2007 issue where the final chapter was published in the September 2011 issue.<ref name="November 2007 Avarus">{{cite web| archiveurl=http://archive.is/aKL4q| archivedate=August 22, 2013| url=http://mag-garden-store.com/shop/shopdetail.html?brandcode=002003000001| title=Monthly Comic Avarus November 2007| publisher=[[Mag Garden]]| language=Japanese| accessdate=August 22, 2013| deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name="September 2011 Avarus">{{cite web| archiveurl=http://archive.is/aDIb2| archivedate=August 22, 2013| url=http://mag-garden-store.com/shop/shopdetail.html?brandcode=002003000047| title=Monthly Comic Avarus September 2011| publisher=[[Mag Garden]]| language=Japanese| accessdate=August 22, 2013| deadurl=no}}</ref> Concurrent to the serialization, Ai Morinaga created side stories which were published in ''[[Comic Blade Masamune|Comic Blade Masamune 2003 Summer Edition]]'' and ''Comic Blade Zebel'' issues 2 to 6.<ref name="CBM 2003 Summer">{{cite web| url=http://www.mag-garden.co.jp/comic-blade/zoukan/zoukan200306.htm| title=''Comic Blade Masamune 2003 Summer Edition'' promotion| publisher=[[Mag Garden]]| language=Japanese| accessdate=September 15, 2013}}</ref><ref name="Zebel 2">{{cite journal| magazine=<U+30B3><U+30DF><U+30C3><U+30AF><U+30D6><U+30EC><U+30A4><U+30C9> Zebel| number=2| date=July 19, 2005<!-- http://blog.livedoor.jp/zebel/archives/2005-07.html#20050719 (Official Zebel blog) -->| publisher=[[Mag Garden]]| language=Japanese}}</ref><ref name="Zebel 6">{{cite web| url=http://www.jbook.co.jp/p/p.aspx/3368054/s/| title=''Comic Blade Zebel'' Vol.6| publisher=Jbook.co.jp| language=Japanese| accessdate=September 15, 2013}}</ref> Mag Garden collected the individual chapters and side stories into eight [[tank<U+014D>bon]] volumes which were released between December 10, 2002 and October 15, 2011.<ref name="Volume 1"/><ref name="Volume 8"/> ''Your and My Secret''{{'}}s plot was properly concluded in {{Nihongo|lit. "My and Her Three X's Extra-Part|<U+50D5><U+3068><U+5F7C><U+5973><U+306E><U+00D7><U+00D7><U+00D7><U+756A><U+5916><U+7DE8>|Boku to Kanojo no Peke Mittsu Bangai-hen}}. Extra-Part was published in Mag Garden's online magazine, Web Comic Beat's, between June 25, 2012 and March 25, 2013.<ref name="Extra Ch1">{{cite web| archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20120628200041/http://comic.mag-garden.co.jp/beats/1981.html| archivedate=June 28, 2012| url=http://comic.mag-garden.co.jp/beats/1981.html| title=''<U+50D5><U+3068><U+5F7C><U+5973><U+306E><U+00D7><U+00D7><U+00D7><U+756A><U+5916><U+7DE8>'' Chapter 1| publisher=[[Mag Garden]]| language=Japanese| accessdate=August 26, 2013}}</ref><ref name="Extra Ch7">{{cite web| archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20130430193359/http://comic.mag-garden.co.jp/beats/1981.html| archivedate=April 30, 2013| url=http://comic.mag-garden.co.jp/beats/1981.html| title=''<U+50D5><U+3068><U+5F7C><U+5973><U+306E><U+00D7><U+00D7><U+00D7><U+756A><U+5916><U+7DE8>'' Final Chapter| publisher=[[Mag Garden]]| language=Japanese| accessdate=August 26, 2013}}</ref> The chapters were later released in a tank<U+014D>bon on May 14, 2013.<ref name="Volume EX"/> Morinaga commented the serialization kept her indoors most of the time and limited her contact with people to her assistant, publisher, supermarket cashiers, and delivery boys.{{gnr|vol|3}}

[[ADV Manga]] licensed the series as ''Your and My Secret'' for North America and released the first volume on July 6, 2004.<ref name="ADV 1"/> [[Tokyopop]] later acquired the license and released the first seven volumes between March 11, 2008 and November 30, 2010.<ref name="TP 1"/><ref name="TP 7"/> After Tokyopop's North American division was closed down, the North American license were returned to Mag Garden.<ref name="Tokyopop Shutdown">{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2011-05-24/tokyopop/japanese-manga-licenses-to-revert-to-owners |title=Tokyopop: Japanese Manga Licenses to Revert to Owners |date=May 24, 2011 |publisher=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=November 13, 2011}}</ref> In 2012, [[JManga]] licensed the series for digital release in English;<ref name="JManga language">{{cite web| archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20130514051251/http://www.jmanga.com/your-my-secret/8| archivedate=May 14, 2013| url=http://www.jmanga.com/your-my-secret/8| title=''Your & My Secret'' Vol. 8| publisher=[[JManga]]| accessdate=August 22, 2013}}</ref> the eight volumes were made available between May 3, 2012 and August 23, 2012.<ref name="JManga 1">{{cite web| url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2012-04-23/jmanga-adds-tactics-monochrome-factor-manga| title=JManga Adds Tactics, Monochrome Factor Manga| date=April 23, 2012| publisher=[[Anime News Network]]| language=Japanese| accessdate=August 22, 2013}}</ref><ref name="JManga 8">{{cite web| url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2012-08-16/jmanga-adds-furumachi-miyoshi-tokyo-lastochika-manga| title=JManga Adds Furumachi Miyoshi's Tokyo Lastochika Manga| date=August 16, 2012| publisher=[[Anime News Network]]| language=Japanese| accessdate=August 22, 2013}}</ref> The manga has also been localized in other languages such as Germany, Italian, Chinese, Thai, Vietnamese, and Spanish.<ref name="German">{{cite web| archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20120304153452/http://www.tokyopop.de/manga-shop/index.php?cPath=9_246| archivedate=March 4, 2012| url=http://www.tokyopop.de/manga-shop/index.php?cPath=9_246| title=''Dein und Mein Geheimnis''| trans_title=Your and My Secret| publisher=[[Tokyopop]]| language=German| accessdate=August 24, 2013| deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name="Italian">{{cite web| url=http://www.starcomics.com/fumetto.aspx?Fumetto=278851| title=''1 Segreto X 2'' volume 8| trans_title=1 Secret X2| publisher=[[Star Comics (Italy)]]| language=Italian| accessdate=August 24, 2013| deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name="Chinese">{{cite web| archiveurl=http://archive.is/72JrU| archivedate=August 27, 2013| url=http://www.2books.com.tw/2hbs/product_info2.php?products_id=1152111| title=''<U+6211><U+611B><U+91CE><U+883B><U+5973><U+53CB>''| publisher=2books.com.tw| trans_title=My Barbaric Girlfriend| language=Chinese| accessdate=August 27, 2013| deadurl=no}}<p>{{cite web| archiveurl=http://archive.is/OMUae| archivedate=August 26, 2013| url=http://www.tongli.com.tw/BookDetail.aspx?Bd=AU01408| title=''<U+6211><U+548C><U+5979><U+7684>XXX''| trans_title=Her and My XXX| publisher=[[Tong Li Publishing]]| language=Chinese| accessdate=August 26, 2013| deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name="Thai">{{cite web| archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20120826212533/http://www.bongkoch.com/catalog/product_info.php?products_id=8926| archivedate=August 26, 2012| url=http://www.bongkoch.com/catalog/product_info.php?products_id=8926| title=''<U+0E40><U+0E21><U+0E37><U+0E48><U+0E2D><U+0E1C><U+0E21><U+0E01><U+0E31><U+0E1A><U+0E40><U+0E18><U+0E2D> XXX'' 8| trans_title=Her and My XXX| publisher=[[Bongkoch Comics]]| language=Thai| accessdate=August 24, 2013| deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name="Vietnamese">{{cite web| archiveurl=http://archive.is/qlcqj| archivedate=August 24, 2013| url=http://vanganhco.vn/DetailSellingManga.aspx?alias=nang-men-chang-bong| title=N<U+00E0>ng Men Ch<U+00E0>ng B<U+00F3>ng| publisher=VanGanhco.vn| language=Vietnamese| accessdate=August 24, 2013}}</ref><ref name="Spanish">{{cite web| url=http://www.amazon.com/dp/8496825272| title=Ser<U+00E1> Nuestro Secreto No 3| publisher=[[Amazon.com]]| accessdate=August 24, 2013| deadurl=no}}</ref> [[Scanlations]] of the Chinese translations popularized the series under the name ''My Barbaric Girlfriend'' ({{zh | c=<U+6211><U+611B><U+91CE><U+883B><U+5973><U+53CB>| hp=W<U+01D2> <U+00E0>i Y<U+011B>m<U+00E1>n N<U+01DA>y<U+01D2>u}}).<ref name="Jason Thompson"/>

