===Radio drama===
Three [[Radio drama in Japan|radio dramas]] based on the manga series were produced. The first radio drama was available for order in ''Monthly Comic Blade''{{'}}s August 2005 issue and is a reenactment of the first five chapters in the series.<ref name="Amazon Comic Blade August 2005">{{cite web| url=http://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B0009XUUKI| title=Monthly Comic Blade August 2005| publisher=[[Amazon.co.jp]]| language=Japanese| accessdate=September 14, 2013}}</ref><ref name="MCB August 2005">{{cite journal| magazine=<U+6708><U+520A><U+30B3><U+30DF><U+30C3><U+30AF><U+30D6><U+30EC><U+30A4><U+30C9>| volume=8| number=2005| date=June 30, 2002| publisher=[[Mag Garden]]| language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.suruga-ya.jp/database/120042450000.html| title=3<U+8A8C><U+9023><U+52D5><U+30AA><U+30EA><U+30B8><U+30CA><U+30EB><U+30C9><U+30E9><U+30DE>CD Blade Edition <U+300C>New Paradise<U+FF06><U+50D5><U+3068><U+5F7C><U+5973><U+306E><U+00D7><U+00D7><U+00D7><U+300D>| trans_title=3 Linked Original Drama CD Blade Edition: New Paradise and Her and My Secret| publisher=Suruga-ya.jp| language=Japanese| accessdate=September 14, 2013}}</ref> The second drama was included with the limited edition of the eighth volume.<ref name="Volume 8 LE"/> It is a reenactment of chapters 29<U+2013>32. The third drama was released with the limited edition of the extra volume.<ref name="Volume EX LE"/> It reenacts the first three chapters in the extra volume.

===Film===
A [[live action]] film based on the manga was released direct to DVD on April 21, 2006 by [[Sega]].<ref name="Movie Drama DVD">{{cite web| url=http://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B000EPFS3K| title=''<U+50D5><U+3068><U+5F7C><U+5973><U+306E><U+00D7><U+00D7><U+00D7>'' [DVD]| publisher=[[Amazon.co.jp]]| language=Japanese| accessdate=August 16, 2013}}</ref> It is directed by Masaki Hamamoto with screenplay by Mikio Satake.<ref name="Drama Staff">{{cite web| archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20060515070013/http://www.peke3.com/staff2.html| archivedate=May 15, 2006| url=http://www.peke3.com/staff2.html| title=''Boku to Kanojo no Peke Mittsu'' staff| publisher=Sega Link| language=Japanese| accessdate=September 17, 2013}}</ref> {{Nihongo foot|Movie Drama My and Her Three X's Visual Guide Book|<U+30E0><U+30FC><U+30D3><U+30FC><U+30C9><U+30E9><U+30DE><U+50D5><U+3068><U+5F7C><U+5973><U+306E><U+00D7><U+00D7><U+00D7><U+3000><U+30D3><U+30B8><U+30E5><U+30A2><U+30EB><U+30AC><U+30A4><U+30C9><U+30D6><U+30C3><U+30AF>|M<U+016B>b<U+012B> Dorama Boku to Kanojo no Peke Mittsu Bijuaru Gaido Bukku|group=Kanji}} is a guide book which provides background production information on the film. It was released before the film on September 28, 2005.<ref name="Movie Drama Book">{{cite web| url=http://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/486127205X/| title=<U+30E0><U+30FC><U+30D3><U+30FC><U+30C9><U+30E9><U+30DE><U+50D5><U+3068><U+5F7C><U+5973><U+306E><U+00D7><U+00D7><U+00D7><U+3000><U+30D3><U+30B8><U+30E5><U+30A2><U+30EB><U+30AC><U+30A4><U+30C9><U+30D6><U+30C3><U+30AF>| publisher=[[Amazon.co.jp]]| language=Japanese| accessdate=August 16, 2013}}</ref> The plot begins similarity to the manga and Akira and Nanako exchange bodies. Manzou gives the two a deadline to raise money in order to rebuild the machine. Akira succeeds but is forced to pay off Nanako's incurring debt. The deadline passes and Manzou leaves Japan, concluding with Akira and Nanako promising to earn enough money for when Manzou returns.

==Reception==
[[Tokyopop]]'s localized volumes appeared on ICv2's monthly top three-hundred selling graphic novels.<ref name="ICv2 Vol3">{{cite web| url=http://www.icv2.com/articles/news/13916.html| title=Top 300 Graphic Novels Actual November 2008| date=December 29, 2008| publisher=ICv2.com| accessdate=September 3, 2013}}</ref><ref name="ICv2 Vol4">{{cite web| url=http://www.icv2.com/articles/news/14313.html| title=Top 300 Graphic Novels Actual January 2009| date=March 5, 2009| publisher=ICv2.com| accessdate=September 3, 2013}}</ref><ref name="ICv2 Vol5">{{cite web| url=http://www.icv2.com/articles/news/18351.html| title=Top 300 Graphic Novels Actual August 2010| date=September 14, 2010| publisher=ICv2.com| accessdate=September 3, 2013}}</ref><ref name="ICv2 Vol6">{{cite web| url=http://www.icv2.com/articles/news/16434.html| title=Top 300 Graphic Novels Actual November 2009| date=January 20, 2010| publisher=ICv2.com| accessdate=September 3, 2013}}</ref><ref name="ICv2 Vol7">{{cite web| url=http://www.icv2.com/articles/news/18919.html| title=Top 300 Graphic Novels Actual November 2010| date=December 7, 2010| publisher=ICv2.com| accessdate=September 3, 2013}}</ref> [[About.com]] readers ranked the series third as Best New Shojo Manga in 2008 and was ranked in the 10 Bizarre Shojo Manga Love Stories in 2010.<ref name="2008 Reader poll">{{cite web| url=http://manga.about.com/od/recommendedreading/tp/2008NewShojoPoll.htm| title=2008 Readers Poll: Best New Shojo Manga| first=Deb| last=Aoki| publisher=[[About.com]]| accessdate=September 3, 2013}}</ref><ref name="Bizarre Shojo">{{cite web| url=http://manga.about.com/od/recommendedreading/tp/StrangeShojoManga.htm| title=Shojo Manga's Weirdest Romances| first=Deb| last=Aoki| publisher=[[About.com]]| accessdate=September 3, 2013}}</ref> [[Jason Thompson (writer)|Jason Thompson]] praised the series for being smart, funny, and unpredictable.<ref name="Jason Thompson">{{Cite web | last=Thompson| first=Jason| url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/house-of-1000-manga/2011-12-15 | title=Jason Thompson's House of 1000 Manga: ''Your and My Secret''| publisher=[[Anime News Network]]| date=December 15, 2011| accessdate= February 8, 2012}}</ref> Pop Culture Shock.com agreed on the humor, and described the series as something all Sh<U+014D>jo fans will enjoy.<ref name="PCP 1">{{Cite web | archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/query.php?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.popcultureshock.com%2Fmanga%2Findex.php%2Freviews%2Fmanga-reviews%2Fweekly-recon-31207%2F| archivedate=July 3, 2010|last=Dacey |first=Katherine |url=http://www.popcultureshock.com/manga/index.php/reviews/manga-reviews/weekly-recon-31207/#yoursecret1 |title=Weekly Recon, 3/12/08: ''Your and My Secret'', Vol. 1 |publisher=Pop Culture Shock | date=March 10, 2008|accessdate=February 8, 2012}}</ref><ref name="PCP 4">{{Cite web | archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/query.php?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.popcultureshock.com%2Fmanga%2Findex.php%2Freviews%2Fmanga-reviews%2Fmanga-minis-5409%2F| archivedate=July 3, 2010 |last=C. |first=Connie |url=http://www.popcultureshock.com/manga/index.php/reviews/manga-reviews/manga-minis-5409/#secret |title=Manga Minis, 5/4/09: ''Your & My Secret'', Vol. 4 |publisher=Pop Culture Shock | date=May 4, 2009|accessdate=February 8, 2012}}</ref> Mania.com described the first volume as an enjoyable read, praised it for the humor and its interesting and realistic approach to the gender swap topic, but expressed annoyance with the protagonist's behavior.<ref name="Mania 1">{{Cite web |last=Lavey |first=Megan |url=http://www.mania.com/your-my-secret-vol-01_article_81670.html |title=''Your and My Secret'' Vol. #01 |publisher=Mania.com |date=July 26, 2004 |accessdate=February 8, 2012}}</ref>  Meanwhile, [[IGN]] panned the plot for being preposterous, citing the protagonists' personalities to be too extreme, and gave no incentive to move past the first volume.<ref name="IGN 1">{{Cite web | archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20120208210928/http://comics.ign.com/articles/870/870247p1.html| archivedate=February 8, 2012|last=Sparrow |first=A. E. |url=http://comics.ign.com/articles/870/870247p1.html |title=''Your and My Secret Volume'' 1 Review| publisher=[[IGN]] |date=April 29, 2008 |accessdate=February 8, 2012| deadurl=no}}</ref>

